track.name: The Sky Was Pink
comments: What a beauty of a track, thank you for creating this so that James Holden could turn it into a masterpiece. Re BoC: BoC is better, but this doesn't really sound much like BoC anyway so I don't know why it's being compared.
Nathan Fake > Bords Of Canada > M83 > Untel

was on a train home from a festival in the summer, in a real stoned blissed out state, put this on, shut my eyes and all i could see was an intense pink glow, the intensity of which moved with the music.
Boards of Canada > M83 > Nathan Fake

One of the most touching and emotional tracks among the minimal-techno genre.
At points it actually sends shivers down my spine.

I try not to listen to it so much, as to not take the chance of it loosing it's magic.

The James Holden remix is also quite good:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_OFkVGywTVA&feature=related

Nathan fake, you are a genius :)
One of the best electronic track ever!!!
almost as nice as my tracks... or maybe not ;-)

one of the best electronica tracks of all time

i can't believe it's not more widely recognised
